The paper deals with the analysis of online algorithms, which is a fundamental topic in computer science. The problem studied in the paper, the two server problem on three colinear points, is a classic problem in online algorithms and falls under the category of computational geometry and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses several measures of algorithm performance, including competitive analysis, which is a common measure in the analysis of online algorithms (cs.AL). The paper also discusses game theory (cs.GT) in the context of the analysis of online algorithms. The paper uses information theory (cs.IT) to analyze the performance of the algorithms. Finally, the paper discusses the worst-case analysis of algorithms, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC).
